00:19:01,592 --> 00:19:04,933
So he's like the father of the UX mindset.

311
00:19:04,933 --> 00:19:07,395
And he has a book called Emotional Design

312
00:19:07,395 --> 00:19:09,395
where he explains a little bit

313
00:19:09,395 --> 00:19:11,016
the three levels of processing

314
00:19:11,016 --> 00:19:13,918
when we interact with an object or a system,

315
00:19:13,918 --> 00:19:18,059
we're gonna process the system

316
00:19:18,059 --> 00:19:18,640
through.

317
00:19:18,800 --> 00:19:24,889
three levels that are going to create some emotions. So the first one is visceral. That's

318
00:19:24,889 --> 00:19:32,840
the level that is very based on appearance. It's like your gut feeling, like the term is pretty

319
00:19:32,840 --> 00:19:33,501
self-explanatory.

320
00:19:34,002 --> 00:19:37,245
It's visceral, so it's how things look.

321
00:19:37,245 --> 00:19:39,888
Bright colors, for example, or how things taste.

322
00:19:39,888 --> 00:19:41,730
The look, feel, the sounds.

323
00:19:41,730 --> 00:19:45,575
This is really like you just look at something

324
00:19:45,575 --> 00:19:47,597
and it looks amazing.

325
00:19:47,597 --> 00:19:48,758
If you're into cars, you know,

326
00:19:48,758 --> 00:19:49,599
they're the cars that.

327
00:19:49,879 --> 00:19:51,900
there's a lot of, um,

