00:20:00,425 --> 00:20:01,626
really feel that they're

332
00:20:01,626 --> 00:20:03,347
powerful. This is all about

333
00:20:03,347 --> 00:20:05,468
visceral design. And so that's

334
00:20:05,468 --> 00:20:08,429
really important in games as

335
00:20:08,429 --> 00:20:09,850
well, of course, and, uh, all

336
00:20:09,850 --> 00:20:11,551
about presentation art, um,

337
00:20:11,551 --> 00:20:14,513
direction, but also game feel

338
00:20:14,513 --> 00:20:15,813
we're going to talk about

339
00:20:16,527 --> 00:20:18,508
The next level is behavioral.

340
00:20:18,508 --> 00:20:21,730
So it's how do we interact with that system?

341
00:20:21,730 --> 00:20:24,792
So it's the pleasure and effectiveness of use.

342
00:20:24,792 --> 00:20:27,534
So this time, it's less about how it looks,

343
00:20:27,534 --> 00:20:28,694
you know, how beautiful it is.

344
00:20:28,694 --> 00:20:30,175
It's not about the aesthetic.

345
00:20:30,175 --> 00:20:31,236
It's about the functionality.

346
00:20:31,236 --> 00:20:34,818
It's about am I able to accomplish the things

347
00:20:34,818 --> 00:20:36,779
